---
title: Lemony Shrimp & Zucchini Couscous with Chives
description: These quick (we’re talking under 30 minutes) couscous bowls are fresh, wholesome, and pack a ton of seafood flavor thanks to a combination of seafood stock and, of course, shrimp. Alongside the shrimp, you’ll sauté subtly sweet zucchini, then finish them both with butter and lots of lemon. Just sprinkle with chives and you’re set!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b87e9fd3e9058428acb40-03aab3da.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673b87e9fd3e9058428acb40-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 400 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1590 mg
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lemony-shrimp-and-zucchini-couscous-673b87e9fd3e9058428acb40
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce}, @Seafood Stock Concentrate{2}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 3.

While couscous cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Quarter @Lemon{1}. Thinly slice @Chives{1/4%ounce}.

Rinse @Shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2%minutes}.

Add shrimp and lightly season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from heat.

> For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches.

Once couscous is finished cooking, add to pan with shrimp and zucchini along with @Butter{2%tbsp} and juice from two lemon wedges. Stir until butter has melted and sauce is creamy, adding splashes of water as needed until everything is coated in sauce.

> TIP: If butter is not melting, return pan to low heat.

Divide lemony shrimp and zucchini couscous between #shallow bowls{}. Garnish with chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.